XLA dumps hlo and mlir modules when run with `XLA_FLAGS=--xla_dump_to=/tmp/foo`. This change updates the locs with the dumped file when doing so, allowing potential errors to reference it.

As a first step, simply replace the locs. During execution, BefFusedLocs and BefNameLocs are turned into OpaqueLocation (just a string), which breaks the source code lookup. The errors therefore reference the tfrt_gpu module just before it's converted to BEF.

[{"sha":"f312bdc59ccbacba236f8cfada4adc12d206f9a2","author":{"email":"b1c859b0203793580f6fafdc9e88d8c10428cc59@google.com","name":"Yang Chen"},"message":"[tf.data service] Propagate infinite cardinality for dynamic sharding.

Dynamic sharding may cause an infinite dataset to be empty, e.g.:

tf.data.Dataset.range(1024).batch(1024, drop_remainder=True).repeat()

In each repetition, the workers will each receive a subset of
`range(1024)` and then drop the partial batch. These cases are
uncommon, and there is a significant performance hit when tf.distribute
sees unknown cardinality instead of infinite. So it's reasonable to
report infinite cardinality in the dynamic sharding case.
